  "texts": [
    "Warmup dataIn this section, we visualize all warmup demonstrations used in our experiments.",
    "As described in the main text, TraceGen is adapted to each task using a lightweight warmup stage, which serves to translate the embodimentagnostic 3D traces into the action space of the target robot or tasks.We consider two warmup regimes: • Robot→Robot (same-embodiment warmup).",
    "Five indomain robot demonstrations are provided for each task.",
    "These clips differ from the evaluation setting in object layout and initial robot pose, ensuring that warmup does not simply memorize target configurations.",
    "• Human→Robot (cross-embodiment warmup)."
